00:45:12,302 --> 00:45:14,202
Does anyone have any questions?

880
00:45:14,202 --> 00:45:14,983
Hello?

881
00:45:14,983 --> 00:45:19,664
So you talked about how the game is inspired

882
00:45:19,664 --> 00:45:23,385
by D&D second edition and classical medieval fantasy,

883
00:45:23,385 --> 00:45:27,427
which I feel like we've been doing for a really long time.

884
00:45:27,427 --> 00:45:30,668
And as a tabletop player, you've probably

885
00:45:30,668 --> 00:45:32,848
been playing all sorts of diverse and interesting

886
00:45:32,848 --> 00:45:34,229
tabletop games.

887
00:45:34,229 --> 00:45:35,930
As a player or a designer, what kind

888
00:45:35,930 --> 00:45:38,510
of these kind of mechanics would you

889
00:45:38,510 --> 00:45:40,111
like to see us bringing into it?

890
00:45:41,092 --> 00:45:42,173
I'm sorry, could you?

891
00:45:42,173 --> 00:45:46,777
So we're still kind of riffing on D&D second edition,

892
00:45:46,777 --> 00:45:49,800
and tabletop gaming has gotten so much bigger and more

893
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:52,303
interesting than that over the last 20 or 30 years.

894
00:45:52,303 --> 00:45:54,906
Is there any of those systems or mechanics

895
00:45:54,906 --> 00:45:56,988
that you'd like to see us bring into our computer games

896
00:45:56,988 --> 00:45:57,748
over the next while?

897
00:45:58,034 --> 00:46:08,157
Yes, so that's a great question. I think for this specific type of game, there are a lot of mechanics that I enjoy from other RPGs that I don't think would necessarily fit in here.

898
00:46:08,157 --> 00:46:17,400
For example, one aspect that I really like about Ars Magica is that it's based around a very long period of time. There's a lot of stuff that you do in downtime.

899
00:46:18,020 --> 00:46:24,905
So every it's about wizards. It's about medieval wizards and you all have a covenant and the covenant is the place where you live and

900
00:46:24,905 --> 00:46:29,568
you protect it and it's important and you have a library and you have resources and

901
00:46:29,568 --> 00:46:34,111
Time is important and you read books to get more powerful reading is power

902
00:46:34,652 --> 00:46:43,234
That's all really cool, but there's a very, very big focus on sort of managing the Covenant and the Grogs and all these other things that go into it.

903
00:46:43,234 --> 00:46:47,795
I don't necessarily know that that's something that's appropriate for a D&D type game, but it's very cool.

904
00:46:47,795 --> 00:46:57,397
I will say though that if you've played the Darkest Dungeon, there are a lot of elements from there that are really similar to Torchbearer, if you've played Torchbearer.

