00:47:02,116 --> 00:47:07,121
I'm sorry, imagine Torchbearer like low level first edition D&D, but harsher.

908
00:47:07,121 --> 00:47:12,125
It's really brutal, I mean that's sort of the darkest dungeon where everyone just spirals

909
00:47:12,125 --> 00:47:14,388
down into insanity and death.

910
00:47:14,388 --> 00:47:18,892
And so, and that's an example I think when you look at Torchbearer, the system design

911
00:47:18,892 --> 00:47:23,136
is so tightly oriented around capturing that feeling, that's very, very cool.

912
00:47:23,136 --> 00:47:25,758
Whereas I think when you look at something like D&D.

913
00:47:26,399 --> 00:47:29,340
D&D, it evolved out of tabletop miniatures gaming.

914
00:47:29,340 --> 00:47:31,601
There's a lot of ideas and systems

