00:51:16,346 --> 00:51:16,386
Oh.

998
00:51:28,531 --> 00:51:32,055
Actually, I have a question more about the tools you use to build a game.

999
00:51:32,055 --> 00:51:37,720
Because if I looked at the Winter Nights, Infinity Engine games, or the Bethesda games,

1000
00:51:37,720 --> 00:51:41,344
a lot of them use global variables and plain text files.

1001
00:51:41,344 --> 00:51:46,790
And I'm just wondering if when building a game like that, doesn't that cause a lot of problems,

1002
00:51:46,790 --> 00:51:48,191
bugs which are difficult to trace?

1003
00:51:48,932 --> 00:51:53,175
Did you use any more custom solutions, something which

1004
00:51:53,175 --> 00:51:56,278
would validate that there are no bugs in the content,

1005
00:51:56,278 --> 00:51:59,080
like a missing global variable or something linking

1006
00:51:59,080 --> 00:52:00,181
to something disappearing?

1007
00:52:00,951 --> 00:52:04,172
So the question is about global variable tracking and things like that.

1008
00:52:04,172 --> 00:52:09,553
So we've tried to build better tools for tracking that stuff over time.

1009
00:52:09,553 --> 00:52:13,535
Most of our data editing used the built-in Unity tools, and that's something that we're

1010
00:52:13,535 --> 00:52:14,755
moving away from now.

1011
00:52:14,755 --> 00:52:17,776
Again, that goes back to file formats and accessibility.

1012
00:52:17,776 --> 00:52:20,357
We want our file formats to be very easy for people to edit.

1013
00:52:20,917 --> 00:52:26,082
But in terms of global variable tracking, we have our own tool set for writing dialogue.

1014
00:52:26,082 --> 00:52:32,008
Again, because Obsidian, Obsidian has, we put a lot of effort into writing and branching dialogues,

1015
00:52:32,008 --> 00:52:33,609
and also tracking quest states.

1016
00:52:33,609 --> 00:52:37,493
So we actually have a quest tool that is specifically for setting up quest flow,

1017
00:52:37,493 --> 00:52:41,317
so you can see how the quest is supposed to actually develop over time.

1018
00:52:41,317 --> 00:52:45,081
And we have a testing tool that allows us to set those variables and track them better.

1019
00:52:45,421 --> 00:52:50,523
So we develop tools for the specific needs of making a very complex role-playing game

1020
00:52:50,523 --> 00:52:55,104
so we can sort of define and track those variables more easily and also test them more easily.

1021
00:52:55,104 --> 00:52:55,804
Does that answer your question?

1022
00:52:55,804 --> 00:52:56,124
Yeah, thank you.

1023
00:52:56,124 --> 00:52:56,764
